{
  "id": 133014,
  "referenceId": 109068,
  "name": "1 John 4:7–21",
  "localizedName": "1 John 4:7–21",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "At the beginning of his "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108031",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "gospel"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", John wrote that no one has ever seen God. Then in John 1:18 he explained that Jesus showed what God is like. What Jesus showed was that God is love."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus made this clear by giving his life to save people from sin. He did this so that they could be saved from death and share life with God for ever. He did this because God loves people. When people believe that Jesus is God’s Son, God lives inside of them. This means that God’s love is inside them."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "John wrote again that no one has ever seen God. But believers can show others what God is like. They can do this because they have God’s love inside of them. This is one way that they are like Jesus. When they show love to others, God’s love is made complete in them."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "God’s love is complete and fulfilled and "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108165",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "perfect"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". That is the kind of love that believers depend on and share with others. There is no hate and nothing to be afraid of in that kind of love."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
